husband who won a grammy last year for living in america when 
he returns from a south american tour this week they had already 
patched things up somewhat before he left she said 
ive had a very very terrible week she said in a telephone 
interview from the couples ranch in beech island sc a few 
miles across the savannah river from augusta ga 
mrs brown who filed for divorce from her husband after she was 
beaten last monday was arrested saturday in the parking lot of 
bush field airport in augusta police said they had been tipped she 
would be receiving a shipment of phencyclidine a hallucinogen also 
called pcp from new york 
she was charged with one felony count of possession of pcp and 
released on 1550 cash bond the same charge was filed against 
ranell t wright 25 of new york who also posted 1550 cash bond 
mrs brown 38 said a friend of one of her husbands employees 
had asked her to pick up ms wright and give her a ride to her 
destination in augusta she declined to identify the person 
it was a setup she said i was framed because they are 
trying to make me drop this case against my husband 
brown 54 was charged with assault with intent to murder and 
