<TEXT>
the outlawed solidarity labor federation 
on sunday said may 1 should be a day of protests against government 
price increases and the lack of union freedom 
in a statement read over the telephone by solidarity adviser 
jacek kuron the unions national executive commission said people 
should boycott official may 1 labor day observances and hold 
demonstrations 
for working people may 1 is the holiday of fighting for 
elementary rights and a day of protest against price increases and 
destruction of independent initiatives a day for struggle for 
union freedoms the statement said 
we desire that may 1 become the symbol of union solidarity so 
that it can demonstrate our demand to regain the rights due us and 
to legalize the free trade union solidarity 
kuron said the commission which met on saturday to approve the 
statement did not specify what form the protests were to take 
solidarity has denounced the price increases imposed by the 
communist government that are expected to raise the costofliving 
in 1988 by more than 40 percent 
solidarity was chartered by the government during nationwide 
strikes in the fall of 1980 but was suspended in december 1981 and 
subsequently outlawed by parliament it had been the only free 
labor federation in the soviet bloc 
