after being imprisoned for 10 days following his arrest on march 
28 when police stopped the protest march he was leading in panama 
city 
gonzalez faced a long prison term on a sedition charge filed by 
the government last summer if he did not accept exile 
he said sunday his arrest last month was totally illegal and 
he had been beaten in prison by military officials 
gonzales said noriega gave him the choice of remaining in jail 
or going into exile 
i accepted exile in order to mobilize latin american public 
opinion against the dictatorship under which panama has lived for 
the past two decades he said 
gonzalez carrying a panamanian flag arrived with his wife 
vilma from panama city he predicted noriegas hold on panama as 
chief of the countrys defense forces soon would end 
general manuel noriega has power but he cannot exercise it 
because the nation wont obey him as a consequence of this 
situation i consider that a change and a return to democracy and to 
the rule of law are bound to come in the next few days gonzalez 
said upon his arrival at maiquetia international airport outside 
caracas 
the only thing that sustains him in power are military arms 
gonzalez said the problem that afflicts us is internal and very 
simple we want freedom and democracy noriega is in the way 
noriega has been indicted on narcotics trafficking charges in 
the united states and washington has imposed economic sanctions 
against panama in an effort to force him to resign 
gonzalez was free on bond on the sedition charge when he was 
arrested during the demonstration he is is one of 35 directors of 
the national civic crusade a coalition of some 200 business 
labor professional and political groups that has been seeking 
noriegas ouster since june 
