president robert mugabes governing 
party decided saturday to merge with former opposition leader 
joshua nkomos party in a further move to establish a oneparty 
socialist state 
more than 3000 zimbabwe african national union patriotic 
front delegates voted at the oneday congress to approve a unity 
accord singed by nkomo and mugabe on dec 22 
they agreed to bring both parties under the governing party 
banner and create a oneparty socialist state in of africas few 
westernstyle democracies 
the entire nation is certainly rejoicing with us today 
mugabe said after the vote 
members of nkomos zimbabwe african peoples union voted 
overwhelmingly april 2 to dissolve the countrys oldest political 
movement and merge nkomos congress also gave support for a 
oneparty socialist state 
mugabe and other officials of nkomos party quit that party in 
1963 vowing to begin a violent struggle for black majority rule in 
what was the whitegoverned british colony of rhodesia 
nkomo 70 and mugabe 64 were detained for over a decade 
without charge as terrorists thousands of their supporters fled 
the country to become guerrillas in their two rival armies during 
the 7yearold war that led to independence as blackgoverned 
zimbabwe on april 18 1980 
