by cosmetics magnate mary kay ash 
although the subsequent oil slump hammered the real estate 
market needham said the dallas market is improving and at least 
two other houses in a similar price range are being built 
we feel very comfortable that the house is going to sell 
needham said in light of todays market we had to go ahead and 
get it finished first if the market had been better we could have 
sold it with just the framing 
the house originally cost 75 million but the price tag was 
raised to 85 million after needham decided to complete the house 
